input_str: The rookie wall is upon us. Well, not us, unless you’re Gustavo Ayon or some other NBA rookie. But it’s that time of year again. Rookies coming out of college played close to 30 games last year. By now, most NBA teams have played 25 to 30 games, and thanks to the breakneck pace of a lockout-shortened season, the rookies are starting to look tired.
